symptom_text: This child had red, swollen eyes, weakness, erythematous skin, questionable difficulty breathing, and a rash.

45 minutes to an hour after administration, while riding home in the car, the patient complained of a headache, became weak, and by history, lost consciousness. He recovered some what when he arrived home; remained weak, required assistance in walking, went to bed, slept for several hours. Normal upon awakening and has had no further problems.
history: ADHD, Speech disorder, Asthma, Erythromycin Allergy.

symptom_text: On past well baby clinic appointment the infant had #2 DTaP, # 2 IPV, and #1 Hib. The mother states that despite the Tylenol, the baby had a seizure which began at 2 PM and got so bad by 6 PM amserv was called. The baby was hospitalized in NICU. Doc 197661 states that mentioned child is being followed by a neurologist and has been placed on anticonvulsants. This physician recommends that the patient receive any immunizations until she is at least 12 months of age.
lab_data: Spinal tap, EEG, Blood work up, patient on PB.
history: Sibling has ADHD; autism and is on Prozac

symptom_text: As the pt and his mother were leaving the office the pt became weak and fell. Mom was concerned about the child's breathing. The pt was brought to the exam room observed and monitored for 1 1/2 hours until stable. The pt laid down flat until stable. Follow up next day.
Pt received vaccines on 9/29/00. Today on 2/15/01, complaining of area of tissue atrophy and hypo-pigmentation 2" X 1" over injection site.
history: ADHD; Allergic Rhinitis; Reaction to insect stings

symptom_text: TC from pt, stating child had a rash on back area, 1 hour, post vax. Told to call MD. When RN called back, client to follow-up on condition. Parent denied rash ever present or TC made to RN; did no visit MD.
This child spiked a temp approximately 1 week later. He became more hyperactive, ceased taking daily naps, between 16 months and 18 months of age. Severe ADHD w developmental delay.
lab_data: Rubeola Ab IgG-pos; Mumps E1A IgG-pos; Rubeola-pos 3.68 ISR "Backed Up" in storage.

symptom_text: The pt experienced an indentation, probably necrosis of the left shoulder.
Upset stomach - 18 hrs post vaccine. Fever 12 hrs later increased 3 degrees- resolved in 2-3 days. emesis-few episodes.
Small area of induration and erythema, tender to palpation.
other_meds: Ritalin; Singulair; Flovent Inhaler; Proventil Inhaler; Cefzil

symptom_text: On 7/19/01, pt had swollen left thigh with rash approximately 10 cm x 8 cm. There were no complaints of pain. Pt given Benadryl for rash and heat packs.

Pt developed a rash and hives on face, arms, chest, back and legs. He had numbness and soreness in right arm and right hand, abdominal pain and vomiting. Symptoms developed within 6 hours, post vax. Pt returned to office and received Benadryl 25mg, IM and observed for 1 hour. Symptoms resolved in office.
other_meds: Clonidine 0.1mg for insomnia; Proventil MDI 2 puffs prn wheezing

symptom_text: On 8/22/01 pt came to clinic with right arm reddened from shoulder to elbow. She was referred to MD. On 8/23/01 pt returned for recheck. The swelling and redness had gone down but it was still warm to touch.
Rash on arm surrounding injection site.

This patient received a flu shot on 10/10/2001 and the following morning broke out in whelps on his back, ear, neck and chest. Saw the doctor 10/11/01. The doctor order Atarax and Patanol for eyes itching and redness. The child also complained of headache and eyes were swollen. Follow up 10/19/2001: "RN confirmed that child was improving when seen in the office morning of October 11; he was given the meds to decrease the time to fully recover from the urticaria and rash.  No other vaccines at this visit, no vaccines in previous 4 weeks, no history of adverse events for child. " Reporter confirmed that child was improving when seen in the office morning of Oct 11: he was given the meds to decrease the time to fully recover from the irticaria and rash. No other vaccines at this visit, no vaccines in previous 4 weeks, no Hx of AE for child.

Guillain-Barre Syndrome developed about 1 month, post vax. Still with symptoms.  Per doc 215039, patient is still "ill" wearing braces + been to hospital several times. Per 1 year follow up: It is unknown if pt has recovered. Any residual symtoms have been updates and sent to CDC 01/03/2003

Approximately 20 minutes after receiving vaccine, "face was twisting, drooling and was unable to talk" according to child's mother (who was called by front office staff at school). Child was taken to ER and received Benadryl injection, was discharged and returned to school the next day.
